{"id": 25520, "date": "1987-01-18T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1987-01-18T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "https://estreetshuffle.com/?p=25520"}, "modified": "2026-06-03T17:36:42", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-04T00:36:42", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-and-bobby-bandiera-willie-and-the-hand-jive", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/01/18/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-bobby-bandiera-willie-and-the-hand-jive/", "title": {"rendered": "Willie and the Hand Jive"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>It&#8217;s not about masturbation, and the insinuation (and at times, accusation) that it was annoyed Johnny Otis to no end.</p>\n<p>But come on: with a title like that, can you blame people for misinterpreting?</p>\n<p>The hand jive was an actual dance, though, originating at a tiny U.K. music venue where audiences were jammed together so tightly that the only part of their body they could move was their hands.</p>\n<p>When Johnny Otis learned of it, he decided to write a song about it. Set to an irresistible Bo Diddley beat, &#8220;Willie and the Hand Jive&#8221; became Otis&#8217; only Top Ten hit in the U.S. And if it hadn&#8217;t been banned by many radio stations for it&#8217;s allegedly off-color lyrics, it might have notched even higher.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/QvOuTInrue0?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>It&#8217;s been covered by countless artists in the years since, including charting versions by Eric Clapton and George Thorogood.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/oRTvQd-CHbg?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/AuNOkGnEme8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>And of course, for children of the seventies, there&#8217;s the unforgettable adaptation by Sha Na Na in <em>Grease</em>.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/fY5pmzmiDO8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8220;Willie and The Hand Jive&#8221; was born for bar bands&#8211;you can jam to it, vamp, and stretch it like Silly Putty. So sooner or later, Bruce was bound to cover it, and that day finally came on a summer evening in 1989 when he joined Bobby Bandiera on stage at Cheers in Long Branch.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/V0bdSzmU4jI?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Bruce and Bobby stretched Otis&#8217; two-and-a-half minute original to a full nine minutes that night, and even as distant as the recording is, we can feel the summer heat of their performance.</p>\n<p>To this day, that remains the only time Bruce is known to have covered &#8220;Willie and the Hand Jive&#8221; in concert.</p>\n<p>(My thanks to podcaster extraordinaire Andrew Hickey for the history lesson&#8211;for a lengthy but fascinating deep-dive into the origin of the hand jive, I highly recommend <a href=\"https://www.500songs.com/e/reupload-episode-71-willie-and-the-hand-jive-by-johnny-otis/\">Episode 71</a> (and all the other ones, too) of his terrific podcast,\u00a0<em>A History of Rock Music in 500 Songs.</em>)</p>\n<p><strong>Willie and the Hand Jive<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> August 2, 1989 (Long Branch, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> August 2, 1989 (Long Branch, NJ)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 February 22, 2021</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>One time only: Bruce covers Johnny Otis&#8217; innocently censored classic, &#8220;Willie and the Hand Jive,&#8221; with Bobby Bandiera on the Jersey Shore.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69672, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_mons